The Church of Markharam

Location: Balenum
Temple Location: Port District
Main deity: Makharam, the Great Kraken
Other notable figures: Holy Mother Varunai
Main tenets: Devotion and honour
Titles: Prior/Prioress, Drowned Ones (worshippers)

The church of Makharam was founded on the shores of Balenum, just when the town was growing in size and wealth eight hundred years ago. 

Worshippers, calling themselves 'Drowned Ones', put their faith in Makharam, who is said to rule over the kraken pods that live near Balenum. They pray to the Great Kraken for calm seas and high seafood yields.
 
Though the tale has changed over the years, it is written that Makharam made a covenant with a human pirate woman he fell in love with named Varunai, now the Holy Mother, in a sacred ceremony called the Ritual of Unity. Their lineage spans across the decades and manifests in potent storm and water magic. Some descendants even wield the ability to speak to the beasts of the sea, or bind them to their will.
 
The Great Kraken's magic is not limited to his descendants. A Ritual of Unity may be completed between a devoted Drowned One, a prior and a willing kraken of Makharam's bloodline. The secret of the ritual is known only to priors and the krakens.
 
In modern times, many families within Balenum worship the Great Kraken. Some may descend from Varunai's bloodline without even knowing it. And others still may wield Makharam's magic without knowing where it comes from.
