Fey Wilds: The Autumn Court

Most citizens of the Autumn Wilds are hybrid creatures native to the three territories, a mix of full animal, humanoid-animal and humanoids. Humans are in the minority here, though elves (Eladrin especially) are common. Each clan is ruled by a Sovereign; the clans warred until 200 years ago, then they called a truce. The Sovereign Triad command the Autumn Court of Magi, powerful magicians gathered from the three clans. Small villages are ruled by a governing noble body loyal to their reigning Sovereign.

The Wilds exist on the material plane, but other planes intercept with the area and warp time/space. South of the Wilds sees a constant twilight, while night encroaches up north. Natives navigate through Trail Stones: magic stones lying at the base of trees that are synched up in a network to guide the wandering Fey traveller through the Wilds' shifting time/space (the Mother Stone lies within the Magi court).

Bear Territory, ruled by Queen Sloane the Bear Queen. The Bear Clan are fiercely territorial and aggressive to outsiders. Races: large beasts/carnivores. Biome: rocky and wintery. Combat specialty: melee.,

